      "playtime_at_review": 20,
      "review_text": "The very first jump made me smile.\nSuch a cute little quirky game.\nfor less than $6 AUD, well worth the smile it gave me.\nThe animations are actually really nice, the subtle foot turn on the glider in idle animation as their head turns, the way their little arms flair out when you jump, theres a lot to love in here.\n\nquirky story, solid platforming, runs well, has great implementation for progression tbh.. I had myself asking how was i even going to reach that area, then the 'unlock' came and it clicked.\n\nThere is a small amount of cheese here, rock hopping, using structures to get somehwere early, which instantly made me think of speed running. \nWould be a kinda dope game for a community 100% speedrun.\n\nAll in all, this game is a small collection of solid lego bricks.\nThe more bricks, the bigger the build, the better the game.\nIts the foundations here that make this game good. This could easily be grown 10x to something bigger or turned 2d side scroller platformer.\n\nWell done guys, absolute banger of a first game.",
      "timestamp_created": 1773797109
    },
    {
      "review_id": "221097650",
